  "verdict": {
    "label": "PATCH NOW",
    "recommendation": "Upgrade spring-framework to 5.3.18+ immediately — CVE-2022-22965 (Spring4Shell) is a CISA KEV-listed RCE with EPSS >97% affecting Tomcat WAR deployments on JDK 9+.",
    "confidence": 0.97,
    "reasoning_summary": "spring-framework 5.3.17 is critically exposed through CVE-2022-22965 (Spring4Shell), a remote code execution vulnerability with CVSS 9.8 that is actively exploited and listed in CISA's KEV catalog. The vulnerability exploits Spring MVC's data binding mechanism to manipulate ClassLoader properties via a specially crafted HTTP request.\n\nThe primary constraint is deployment context: exploitation requires the application to be deployed as a WAR on Apache Tomcat with JDK 9+, and the attacker must be able to send HTTP requests to the application. Spring Boot executable JARs are not vulnerable to the published exploits. Operators should confirm their deployment topology before determining urgency — WAR-on-Tomcat deployments are CRITICAL, JAR deployments should still patch but are not currently exposed to known exploits.\n\nCVE-2022-22950 (SpEL DoS) and CVE-2022-22970 (file upload DoS) are lower-severity findings with no active exploitation evidence. Both are addressed by the same patch as Spring4Shell.\n\nFix: upgrade to 5.3.18 or 5.2.20 to resolve all three CVEs in a single patch cycle.",
